sudo apt-get install nodejs

One more recommendation Iâ€™d like to make is that you use binstubs. You can set your application up with binstubs by running bundle --binstubs. This will create a bin/ directory in your application root with all of the executables for the gems in your Gemfile. Having binstubs will make development easier: you can set your PATH by add the following line to your ~/.bashrc or ~/.bash_profile:
PATH=./bin:$PATH
